Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Composer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-7)

Page settings allow, in addition to specifying the paper format, detailed setting of each of the page margins and page extents of the different document areas. The Page settings panel can be always found in the right panel &gt; Styles &gt; Page settings.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Page settings panel*

The panel which is shown in the figure above, is divided into the following sections:

- Master

In other words page dimensions or page master. It defines the document boundaries, which usually go along with the paper format being used.

Click the drop-down menu and select the paper format (page master) you want. This is possible only if the page sequence is not protected - meaning when page sequence is editable. You may choose only from existing page masters predefined in the template by Template Designer. In case the page master itself is also editable in the Composer you may use Format drop-down to choose from available standardized options like A4 and A3. Alternatively choose Custom and used both text fields Page width/height for individual settings.

- Page Margins

Define the distances from the above page boundaries to the actual page body. The following input fields are available:

Top  sets the distance to the top edge of the page

- Bottom  sets the distance to the bottom edge of the page

- Left  sets the distance to the left edge of the page

- Right  sets the distance to the right edge of the page

- Body Margins

Defines the distances from the page margin to the page content. This setting is useful to reserve space for possible Header and Footer insertion, or conversely to remove the space when Header and Footer are not in use.

The following input fields can be specified:

Top  gives the distance from the top page margin

- Bottom  gives the distance from the bottom page margin

- Left - gives the distance from the left page margin

- Right  gives the distance from the right page margin

- Extents

With the extent settings you can define the distances of both regions for header and footer regions in relation to the body margins.

The following settings are available:

Top  sets the distance from the top page margin, which is used for the header region

- Bottom  sets the distance from the bottom page margin, which is used for the footer region

If you use header and/or footer regions in your document then the values used here for top and/or bottom should not be smaller than those defined for the

body margins, in order to avoid overlapping with body margins.

## Headers and Footers
Header and Footer allow repeatable header and footer areas to be automatically produced.
